<h6></h6>

<p>To determine the dust profile for a hole which has not been logged, we interpolate or extrapolate using the eight dust logs as reference points.  Holes within the convex hull defined by the logs can be interpolated with a standard natural neighbor method (Delaunay tessellation), while holes outside must be extrapolated, here we use a modified ridge estimator.  <i>Extrapolated dust profiles</font></i> for strings not enclosed by dust logs, e.g. 75-78, <i>should be treated with caution.</i>  Note that Hole 21 was only logged to 2113 m, so the bottom ~350 meters in the southeast corner is to some extent an extrapolation.</p>
