<center><h4><u>Ash Layers</u></h4></center>
From these images and dust logs made at Siple Dome (West Antarctica) and Dome C (East Antarctica), together with ice core measurements, we can identify certain depositions at South Pole to be volcanic.  We currently have around 20 candidate ash layers, with roughly half lying at IceCube instrumented depths.
